===Etymology===
Hello (first attested in 1884) < ''[[hallo]]'' (attested 1840) < ''holla'', ''hollo'' (attested 1588). This variant of ''[[hallo]]'' is credited to [[w:Thomas Edison|Thomas Edison]] as a coinage for telephone use. Alexander Graham Bell had favored ''[[ahoy|ahoy-hoy]]''.

HI 


Hi mean Hello and hello means Hi

